QUEUE (Fifo)
PS: Must rename [Fifo] to [queue]

First-In First-Out queue.
A FIFO stores values and returns them in the same order they were inserted.
Example:
text
A
B
C

Inserted in this order:
text
push(A)
push(B)
push(C)

Retrieved in this order:
text
A
B
C

FIFO is useful for:
• UART transmit buffers
• UART receive buffers
• keyboard buffers
• event queues
• packet queues
• producer / consumer systems
There is no panel UI in v1 — logic only.

