Stack
comp [stack] is a Last-In-First-Out (LIFO) storage component.
The last value pushed into the stack is the first value returned when popping.
Stacks are commonly used for:
• CPU call stacks (CALL / RET)
• Expression evaluation
• Temporary value storage
• Undo/redo systems
• State saving and restoration
Internally, stack uses the same storage engine as comp [queue], but operates in LIFO mode instead of FIFO mode.

