Relationship to Queue
comp [stack] and comp [queue] share the same underlying storage implementation.
Conceptually:
text
comp [queue]

operates in:
text
FIFO

mode.

───

text
comp [stack]

operates in:
text
LIFO

mode.

───

This distinction exists to keep the language aligned with the terminology used in computer architecture and data structures while reusing the same storage model internally.

